Author:  BOREHAM
Vol / Page:  103
Edition:
Quote:   [Reference 1850s] More than once he [Selwyn] rushed, half-clothed, into some little bush settlement at dead of night. In his hand was a

ballarat - an impromptu lantern, consisting of an inverted bottle with the bottom broken off, and a [104] candle fixed in the neck.
